8 "skilled manual",  9 "semi-unskilld manual",  10 "farm labor",11 "selfempl farm". The recoded variable is labeled using {cmd:egp10}as {it:lblname}; see help {help label}.{p 0 4}{help isko8868} transforms ISCO-88 codes intoISCO-88 codes; cf ILO (1990).{title:Options}{p 0 4}{cmd:isko} specifies the variable to be recoded.This must be a 4 digit integer containing ISCO-88 occupational codes.{p 0 4}{cmd:sempl} specifies a variable indicating whether or notthe respondent is self-employed. A 1 indicates self-employment, all othervalues are ignored. Applies only to {cmd:iskoegp}.{p 0 4}{cmd:supvis} specifies a variable indicating the number of employeesthe respondent supervises. The values 1 and 10 are significant forplacement in certain EGP categories. Applies only to {cmd:iskoegp}.{title:References}{p 0 4}Erikson, R., J.H. Goldthorpe, L. Portocarero. 1979.{it:International class mobility in three Westen European Countries:England, France, and Sweden.}British Journal of Sociology 30: 415-451.{p 0 4}Ganzeboom, H.B.G., de Graaf, P.M. & D.J. Treiman. 1992.{it:A Standard International Socio-Economic Index of Occupational Status.}Social Science Research 21: 1-56.{p 0 4}ILO (International Labour Office). 1968.{it:International Standard Classification of Occupations, revised edition.}Geneva: International Labour Office.{p 0 4}{c -}{c -}. 1990.{it:International standard classification of occupations: ISCO-88.}Geneva: International Labour Office.{p 0 4}Treiman, D.J. 1977.{it:Occupational Prestige in Comparative Perspective.}New York: Academic Press.Direct comments to:{p 4 4}{browse "mailto:John_Hendrickx@yahoo.com": John Hendrickx}{break}Management Studies Group{break}Wageningen University{break}Hollandseweg 1{break}6706 KN Wageningen{break}The Netherlands{break}{p}The {cmd:isko} package is available at{browse "http://ideas.uqam.ca/ideas/data/bocbocode.html":SSC-IDEAS}.Use {help ssc} {cmd:install isko} to obtain th